11/09/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The government announced on Wednesday (10 September) that the United States has donated a 278,000-euro machine that will be used to remove antipersonnel mines along Albania's border with Kosovo. At least 27 people have been killed and more than 200 injured in accidents involving the mines, planted by Yugoslav forces during the Kosovo conflict.
In other news, Albanian Chief of Staff General Pellumb Qazimi announced Wednesday that there is no urgent need to cut army staff. He said that any downsizing associated with military reforms would be a gradual process. (AFP, Albanian Daily News - 10/09/03)
